#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:16
msgid "Register an OAuth app in Zoom"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:18
msgid "A Zoom system admin must perform the following steps in Zoom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:20
msgid ""
"Zoom supports OAuth authentication, and there are 2 types of OAuth Zoom "
"Apps you can register: **Account-Level** and **User-Level**. You can use "
"either type based on your organization's security and preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Account-Level**: Individual users in Mattermost are verified by "
"checking their Mattermost email and requesting their Personal Meeting ID "
"via the Zoom API. The user's email address in both Mattermost and Zoom "
"must match. Create a User Level Zoom app instead if you prefer that each "
"user to authorize individually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:23
msgid ""
"**User-Managed**: Individual users in Mattermost are required to "
"authorize the Mattermost App to access their Zoom account. Create an "
"Account-Level app instead if you prefer that an admin authorizes access "
"on behalf of the whole Zoom organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:27
msgid ""
"Complete the following steps to create an account-level Zoom app for "
"Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:29 ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:42
msgid "Go to https://marketplace.zoom.us/ and log in as an admin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:30
msgid "In the top right, select **Develop** and then select **Build App**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:31 ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:44
msgid ""
"On top, select **Development**. We would choose **Production** if we were"
" publishing to marketplace, but we won't be doing that here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:32 ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:45
msgid ""
"You can edit the name of your app from top left side by clicking on edit "
"icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:33
msgid "Choose **Admin-managed app** as the app type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:34 ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:47
msgid ""
"Next you'll find your **Client ID** and **Client Secret**. Please copy "
"this as these will be needed when you set up Mattermost to use the "
"plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:35 ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:48
msgid ""
"Enter a valid **Redirect URL for OAuth** "
"\\(`https://SITEURL/plugins/zoom/oauth2/complete`\\) and add the same URL"
" under **Add Allow List**. Note that `SITEURL` should be your Mattermost "
"server URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:36
msgid ""
"To add user scopes to the app, select **Scopes**, and add the following "
"scopes: ``meeting:read:meeting:admin``, "
"``meeting:write:meeting:admin``,and ``user:read:user:admin``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:40
msgid ""
"Complete the following steps to create a user-managed Zoom app for "
"Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:43
msgid "In the top right select **Develop** and then **Build App**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:46
msgid "Choose **User-managed app** as the app type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:49
msgid ""
"To add user scopes to the app, select **Scopes**, and add the following "
"scopes: ``meeting:read:meeting``, ``meeting:write:meeting``,and "
"``user:read:user``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:52
msgid "Configure webhook events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:54
msgid ""
"When a Zoom meeting ends, the original post shared in the channel can be "
"automatically changed to indicate the meeting has ended and how long it "
"lasted. To enable this functionality, create a webhook subscription in "
"Zoom that tells the Mattermost server every time a meeting ends. The "
"Mattermost server then updates the original Zoom message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:56
msgid ""
"While editing the app in Zoom, select **Access** under the **Features** "
"tab on the left."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:57
msgid ""
"Select **Add New Event Subscription**, and give it a name, such as "
"``Meeting Ended``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:58
msgid ""
"Enter a valid **Event notification endpoint URL** "
"``https://SITEURL/plugins/zoom/webhook?secret=WEBHOOKSECRET``, replacing "
"``SITEURL`` with your Mattermost URL. ``WEBHOOKSECRET`` is generated "
"during `Mattermost configuration <#mattermost-configuration>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:59
msgid "Select **Save** to save the webhook configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:60
msgid ""
"Copy the **Secret Token** value at the top of the page for use in the "
"next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:63
msgid "Mattermost configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:65
msgid "A Mattermost system admin must perform the following steps in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:67
msgid "Install the Zoom integration from the in-product App Marketplace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:71
msgid ""
"We recommend making a copy of your webhook secret and encryption key, as "
"it will only be visible to you once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:73
msgid ""
"In Mattermost, from the Product menu |product-list|, select **App "
"Marketplace**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../<rst_prolog>:100
msgid ""
"Navigate between Channels and collaborative playbooks using the product "
"menu icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:74
msgid "Search for or scroll to Zoom, and select **Install**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:75
msgid ""
"Once installed, select **Configure**. You'll be taken to the System "
"Console."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:76
msgid ""
"On the Zoom configuration page, enable and configure Zoom "
"interoperability as follows, and then select **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:77
msgid ""
"For self-hosted Zoom deployments, enter the **Zoom URL** and **Zoom API "
"URL** for the Zoom server when you're using a self-hosted private cloud "
"or on-premises Zoom server, such as ``https://YOUR-ZOOM.com`` and "
"``https://api.YOUR-ZOOM.com/v2`` respectively, replacing ``YOUR-ZOOM`` "
"with your Zoom server URL. Leave this field blank if you're using Zoom's "
"vendor-hosted SaaS service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:78
msgid ""
"If you've created an `account level Zoom app for Mattermost <#register-"
"an-oauth-app-in-zoom>`__, set **OAuth by Account Level App** to **true**."
" Leave this value as **false** if you've created a user level Zoom app "
"for Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:79
msgid ""
"Connect your users to Zoom using OAuth. Enter the **Client ID** and "
"**Client Secret** generated when `registering the oauth app in Zoom "
"<#register-an-oauth-app-in-zoom>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:80
msgid ""
"Select **Regenerate** next to the **At Rest Token Encryption Key** field "
"to generate an AES encryption key. You just need to generate this value, "
"and won't use it anywhere else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:81
msgid ""
"If you're configuring webhook events, select **Regenerate** next to the "
"**Webhook Secret** field. This is the ``WEBHOOKSECRET`` value to use in "
"your webhook URL pointing to Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:82
msgid ""
"Paste the **Secret Token** from the Zoom webhook configuration page into "
"the plugin setting **Zoom Webhook Secret**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/integrate/zoom.rst:83
msgid "Select **Save** to save your changes."
msgstr ""

